Tzatziki

1/2 cup greek yogurt (brand: fage)
1/2 medium cucumber, peeled, seeded, and diced fine (about 1/2 cup)
1/8 teaspoon table salt
and another
1/4 teaspoon table salt
1 teaspoon fresh lemon juice
1 garlic clove pressed through a garlic press
1/2 teaspoon dried dill (or 1 tablespoon of fresh)

1. Combine cucumber, 1/8 teaspoon salt, and lemon juice in colander set over bowl and let stand 30 minutes. In a hurry - skip this step, you'll have runnier sauce.
2.Combine yogurt, drained cucumber, remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt, garlic, and mint in clean bowl. 


Alternative Tzatziki
via http://greekfood.about.com/od/appetizerssalads/r/tzatziki_sass.htm

16 ounces (2 cups) of thick Greek yogurt
4 to 10 cloves of garlic, finely chopped
1/2 cup of diced or grated cucumber (Kirby or "English")
1 tablespoon of olive oil
2 teaspoons of lemon juice
Dill

Prepare all ingredients in advance.

Combine oil and lemon juice in a medium mixing bowl.

Fold the yogurt in slowly, making sure it mixes completely with the oil.

Add the garlic, according to taste, and the cucumber. Stir until evenly
distributed. Garnish with a bit of green and serve well chilled. 
